About UV Gullas College of Medicine

UV Gullas College of Medicine is one of the{" "} top Philippines medical college {" "} which was established in 1919. It is one of the best choices for studying MBBS because the students will get clinical training at the Central Philippines medical centre. This college is approved by the MCI & WHO and the students will be awarded Medical doctor degree after completing MBBS in UV Gullas College of Medicine. The process of{" "} MBBS in Philippines 2020 is very easy & the students can pursue{" "} MBBS in UV Gullas College of Medicine at reasonable fees . The duration of MBBS in the Philippines is 6 years which includes 5 years of MBBS course & 1 year of internship.

Indian Student Admission Procedure

Indian students need to follow the below steps to study{" "} MBBS in Philippines 2020:

  • {" "} The students need to submit the application to the chairman of the committee with all the required documents to the secretary.
  • {" "} The orientation program is conducted for the students and their parents/guardian.
  • {" "} Then the interview will be conducted by the scholarship committee.
  • {" "} When the students are selected, they must sign the contract of the scholarship.

Eligibility Criteria of UV Gullas College of Medicine

The eligibility criteria of the students who want to study MBBS in Philippines medical college are as follows:

  • {" "} The students should have science in their 12th standard and should have an aggregate of 50% marks in physics, chemistry, and Biology.
  • {" "} The students should be at least 17 years of age to study{" "} MBBS in Philippines 2020.
  • {" "} The students should also qualify for the NEET exam with passing marks to apply for taking admission to{" "} MBBS in Philippines 2020.
  • {" "} The students should have English subject in their higher secondary.
  • {" "} The students must not be more than 25 years of age.
Requirements for MBBS Admission

The necessary documents for taking admission to{" "} MBBS in Philippines 2020 are the following:

  • {" "} A complete filled application form with all accurate details.
  • {" "} Original and photocopies of Passport.
  • {" "} Birth certificates and other mandatory certificates must be submitted to the concerned authority.
  • {" "} Passport size (3cmX4cm) photographs.
  • {" "} Original and a photocopy of mark sheets of both 10th & 12th standard
  • {" "} A scorecard of NEFT (if required)
  • {" "} Transfer certificate from the previous school
  • {" "} Leaving certificate from the concerned school
  • {" "} A certificate of code of conduct must be submitted
  • {" "} The bank copy of guardians must be submitted which indicates that they have sufficient funds to pay the fees to UV Gullas College of Medicine.
  • {" "} A medical checkup certificate is also essential
